         Read some link to a Mac gaming site that said that the Mac version will be incompatible with the PC version in that they have their own servers.  This makes sense when you think of the tight coupling between the client and server software.  It would be a nightmare for them to keep the PC and Mac versions in sync AND release frequent patches to both.</P><P>It concerns me that there will be an awfull lot of different EQ worlds to support.  This is the current list:</P><P>Everquest PC (the one we are playing)<BR>Everquest Mac<BR>Everquest PlayStation2<BR>Everquest II PC</P><P>Not to mention an off-shoot group developing Star Wars Galaxies and probably in multiple editions as well.</P><P>Me thinks that there are not enough shut-ins to keep all of these games alive.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
