			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=1850')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=50802&amp;TOPIC_ID=6134&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=EQ+porting+to+Mac++%3B%2F&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Let's think about this logically here.  The reason Sony is going to the trouble of porting this to the Mac, is because they want to have EQ2 for the Mac very soon after launch of EQ2 for the PC.  They want the experience of working with the platform, before the real target begins.  They have NO competition on the Mac and will make up their investment.</P><P>Just like the new engine in SoL was a early test for EQ2 engine.  They have a game that generates enough interest where gamers don't mind having to beta test code.  It's that simple.  Also, VI doesn't have to make 1050 MB worth of changes to the code.  The textures, which occupy the most space, will basically remain the same except for possibly a different compression technology.  Nvidia and ATI are the only Graphics card players for the Mac and I'm sure are working very closely with VI to make those changes.  VI will have to rewrite the engine to compensate for the Mac graphics API's.  This is no small task, but EQ is not the first 3d game to go to the Macintosh.  The game rules, though, will remain essentially unchanged.  Also, with OS X, this will make the port much simpler than to the legacy OS 9, 8, etc.  The Unix base makes a big difference.  </P><P>And losing 100,000 subscribers between years 2 and 3 of a MMORPG when they no longer have the best graphics and there have been many challengers to go after their crown.  This game has surpassed any wildest dream any of the original team ever had. 400,000 subscribers for a 3 year old game is simply staggering.  </P><P></P><P>Wurtin<BR>59th lvl Defiler of E'ci</P><P>“All that is necessary for the triumph of evil is for good men to do nothing.” Edmund Burke<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
